| Entity | Real? | Storage | MongoDB? | Maturity | New signal |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| mybrains.ai (Brains) | ✅ | Postgres+pgvector (RLS) | ❌ | Live hosted product | Consumer MCP memory + Codex app store + mini-sites |
| Memclaw / Caura | ✅ | Postgres+pgvector+Redis | ❌ (OSS Apache-2.0) | OSS+managed, eToro case, SOC2-in-progress | Governance (Keystones, trust tiers) + SKILL.md open standard |
| Qontext | ✅ | Graph+vector (undisclosed) | ❌ unconfirmed | $2.7M pre-seed, Berlin | Graph-first context vaults; top-tier angel validation |
| Caura Medium article | ✅ (same as Memclaw) | n/a | n/a | Blog | SKILL.md portable skill format |
| factory.ai AutoWiki | ✅ | Markdown (GitHub Wiki + Factory App) | ❌ | Live, official docs | "Wiki as CI build artifact on every push" |
| groundedwork (Idan Shimon) | ❌ vapor | unknown | unknown | No public artifact | none — flag for re-check |
| Confluence Rovo MCP | ✅ (Atlassian GA) | Atlassian Cloud (Rovo Teamwork Graph) | ❌ | GA, official | SaaS-vendor MCP servers as ingest connectors |

## MongoDB signal
**Zero of 7 entities are MongoDB-based.** The only MongoDB mentions were (a) a web_search-synthesized fabrication about mybrains.ai citing a 404 URL (`mybrains.ai/brain.html`), and (b) a SourceForge mirror + AI-synthesized "MemClaw on MongoDB blueprint" — neither reflects actual code (Postgres+pgvector). **Open whitespace for memongo: the company-brain / agent-memory category is Postgres+pgvector dominated; no funded competitor has claimed the MongoDB Atlas unified doc+vector+graph position.**

## Gaps
- Qontext exact storage engine undisclosed (graph-DB lean from Neo4j-founder angel, unconfirmed).
- groundedwork: cannot confirm existence — needs original report author to supply URL/repo/screenshot. Possibly private/stealth or misremembered name.
- Oz Madar Rovo "works wonders with Claude" quote: no primary source; integration real, testimonial unverifiable.
- mybrains.ai: "Postgres" inferred from RLS language, not literally stated — recommend checking their jobs page/engineering blog for stack confirmation.

